        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Now I remember what I was going to say...</P><P>Verant really needs to rethink their testing process imo, if they have one at all.  The fact is, look at how many things are broken with the release of SoL, how many patches had to be put in, etc.  Also, look at (for example) the Spell Casting Fury skill (and the thread on this board about how no doubt it will get nerfed).  I bet it does happen, but only because Verant didn't seem to test the skills well, and as such they will feel that the crits are happening too often, or are doing too much damage.  A little bit of testing on their part would eliminate the need for nerfs like this later on.</P><P>Dire charm is another example, and it can go both ways... first way is the fact that it is broken as it is.  Second way is that they will no doubt feel in the future that the skill is too powerful and will nerf it in some way.  Again, proper testing would eliminate this need.  In hindsight, this phrase applies to a lot of things in EQ (alchemy, monk FD, rogue issues, etc etc etc).</P><P>They also really need to redo their PR/IR.  Yes, way back when, Flameplay was the cesspool of the EQ community, but it is imo even worse now, as no one has any decent way to voice their opinions and/or get feedback.  Mythic (DAoC) is doing a great job (despite me not playing the game) as their devs post often and frequently on the CamelotVault message boards, and they have Sanya (can't remember last name) as their PR/IR person who posts a hell of a lot.  I thought Verant hired Absor for that kind of work, and quite frankly it seems to me like he's doing a pretty piss poor job.  On the other hand, Verant's policy may very well be "Stay away from the customers as much as you can".  *shrug*</P><P><img src="http://www.the-den.org/eq/z-small.jpg" border=0><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45366" target="_New">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45366</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

